    <note>Shen(2) Liao [1453] Fu's [7324] son, Zhou's [7323] nephew, Gua's [1450] and Pei's [1456] cousin. He used his elder brother Gou's [1449] yin to enter the civil service. Zhang(1) Feng's [7011] son-in-law. Zhang(1) Mian's [262] grandson-in-law. He once lived in Suzhou. The author of his funerary inscription was married to his younger sister and his son was one of Liao's sons-in-law. Another son-in-law, Ma(2) Yongyu [3669], was a member of Ma(2) Liang's [1349] lineage. The third son-in-law was a Suzhou Zhang(1) Shouguang [3160], possibly a member of the lineage of Liao's father-in-law, Zhang(1) Feng [7011]. Liao's career was advanced through two recommendations by Wu(3) Chong [1960]. XCB, 228.5b; Shen Shi san, 61.78b; Suzhou FZ, 139.20b. CBD, 1, 687.</note>
